.SH EXAMPLE
.sp
To checkpoint the cluster with jobid 256841 in the \fB$HOME/ckpt1/\fP directory:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
pcocc ckpt \-j 256841 $HOME/ckpt1/
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
This produces a disk and a memory image for each VM:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
ls ./ckpt1/
disk\-vm0  disk\-vm1  memory\-vm0  memory\-vm1
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
